00:00:03.500 --> 00:00:07.080
Noodles with his hands

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:11.640
Hello to all our viewers to the channel!

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:18.240
Now I will tell you how to cook noodles for soup at home.

00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:20.480
This will require:

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:25.820
1 egg;

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:33.760
half a teaspoon of salt;

00:00:34.540 --> 00:00:38.180
from 110 to 120 grams of flour dough.

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:49.120
Salt and need to stir the egg.

00:00:55.540 --> 00:01:04.880
110 -120 grams of flour - 2 tablespoons is with a very large hill.

00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:16.880
The flour is mixed with beaten egg and salt.

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:43.040
It turns out the dough.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.240
More 1 tablespoon of flour needed to pour on the table.

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:55.640
And put the dough on the flour.

00:01:55.640 --> 00:02:00.520
The dough should be cool.

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:15.040
The dough is kneaded by hand.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:43.000
The dough was uniform.

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:58.560
The dough should be a rolling pin to roll out a large.

00:03:24.800 --> 00:03:37.960
In the process of rolling out the dough should be sprinkled with flour.

00:03:37.960 --> 00:03:45.520
The dough should not stick to the table.

00:03:51.440 --> 00:04:02.160
The thickness of the resulting dough sheet should be from 0.3 to 0.5 millimeters.

00:04:04.840 --> 00:04:09.760
Sheet of dough sprinkled with flour again.

00:04:09.920 --> 00:04:15.080
And folds.

00:04:15.080 --> 00:04:24.440
Cutting board sprinkled with flour.

00:04:27.080 --> 00:04:38.600
The dough is cut into strips 1-3 mm in width.

00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:56.840
Noodles get very dry.

00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:08.800
Noodles can be used immediately.

00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:16.840
Also, the noodles may be dried and used later.

00:05:26.680 --> 00:05:37.200
This amount is enough to cook the noodles 2 liters of soup.

00:05:48.560 --> 00:05:52.320
Thank you for watching!

